    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Vincetoxicum lateriflorum are its anti-inflammatory effects, which are due to the presence of flavonoids such as quercetin and kaempferol. This plant has also been shown to exhibit antioxidant activity, attributed to the bioactive compounds of saponins and phenolic acids. The anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties of Vincetoxicum lateriflorum contribute to its hepatoprotective effects, which are beneficial for the treatment of liver diseases. Moreover, the plant's volatile oils, including borneol and bornyl acetate, contribute to its sedative and anxiolytic properties, providing relief from anxiety and stress. Additionally, the flavonoids and phenolic acids present in Vincetoxicum lateriflorum have been found to exhibit antimicrobial activity, making it a potential agent for the treatment of infections.",
