    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Vincetoxicum lateriflorum are vincetoxicum tincture, vincetoxicum infusion, vincetoxicum tea, vincetoxicum decoction, and vincetoxicum extract. Vincetoxicum tincture is a concentrated liquid extract made by soaking the plant material in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin, typically used in small amounts as a treatment for various health issues. Vincetoxicum infusion and tea are prepared by steeping the plant material in hot water, the former typically being more concentrated than the latter, with both used to support health and well-being. Vincetoxicum decoction is a more intense preparation made by boiling the plant material in water, often used to extract more of the plant's bioactive compounds. Vincetoxicum extract is a concentrated powder or liquid made using various extraction methods, such as solvent extraction or cold pressing, and is used to provide a standardized dose of the plant's active compounds.",
